<mxfile host="app.diagrams.net" agent="Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Ubuntu; Linux x86_64; rv:138.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/138.0" version="27.0.8" scale="1" border="0"> <diagram name="Page-1" id="wNi5590o-G6y4PK809yC"> <mxGraphModel dx="5915" dy="-646" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="850" pageHeight="1100" math="0" shadow="0"> <root> <mxCell id="0" /> <mxCell id="1" parent="0" /> <UserObject label="" plantUmlData="{
 "data": "@startuml
title Rwanda Infrastructure Management System

start

:Application Starts;

:Load data from files (cities.txt, roads.txt) if they exist;
if (Files do not exist or loading fails) then (yes)
 :Initialize empty city list;
 :Initialize empty adjacency matrices (roads & budgets);
 :Initialize nextCityId = 1;
else (no)
 :Populate city list from cities.txt;
 :Determine max city ID and set nextCityId;
 :Resize adjacency matrices based on loaded cities;
 :Populate road and budget matrices from roads.txt;
endif

repeat
 :Display Main Menu:
 1. Add new city(ies)
 2. Add roads between cities
 3. Add the budget for roads
 4. Edit city
 5. Search for a city using its index
 6. Display cities
 7. Display roads (adjacency matrix)
 8. Display recorded data on console
 9. Exit;
 :User enters choice (1-9);

 switch (choice)
 case (1)
 :User selected \"Add new city(ies)\";
 :Prompt \"Enter the number of cities to add:\";
 :User enters N;
 if (N > 0) then (yes)
 :currentMaxId = current number of cities;
 :newSize = currentMaxId + N;
 :Resize roadAdjacencyMatrix to newSize x newSize;
 :Resize budgetAdjacencyMatrix to newSize x newSize;
 :Loop N times (for city i from 1 to N);
 :Prompt \"Enter name for city \" + nextCityId + \":\";
 :User enters cityName;
 :Validate cityName (is it unique?);
 if (Unique) then (yes)
 :Add city (nextCityId, cityName) to list;
 :nextCityId++;
 :Log \"City added successfully\";
 else (no)
 :Log \"City name already exists. Try again.\";
 :Decrement loop counter (or handle retry);
 endif
 :EndLoop;
 else (no)
 :Log \"Invalid number of cities.\";
 endif
 case (2)
 :User selected \"Add roads between cities\";
 :Prompt \"Enter the name of the first city:\";
 :User enters city1Name;
 :Prompt \"Enter the name of the second city:\";
 :User enters city2Name;
 :Get city1Id from city1Name;
 :Get city2Id from city2Name;
 if (city1Id valid AND city2Id valid AND city1Id != city2Id) then (yes)
 :roadAdjacencyMatrix[city1Id-1][city2Id-1] = 1;
 :roadAdjacencyMatrix[city2Id-1][city1Id-1] = 1;
 :Log \"Road added between \" + city1Name + \" and \" + city2Name;
 else (no)
 :Log \"Error: One or both cities not found, or cities are the same.\";
 endif
 case (3)
 :User selected \"Add the budget for roads\";
 :Prompt \"Enter the name of the first city:\";
 :User enters city1Name;
 :Prompt \"Enter the name of the second city:\";
 :User enters city2Name;
 :Get city1Id from city1Name;
 :Get city2Id from city2Name;
 if (city1Id valid AND city2Id valid AND city1Id != city2Id) then (yes)
 if (roadAdjacencyMatrix[city1Id-1][city2Id-1] == 1) then (yes)
 :Prompt \"Enter the budget for that road (in Billions RWF):\";
 :User enters budgetValue;
 :budgetAdjacencyMatrix[city1Id-1][city2Id-1] = budgetValue;
 :budgetAdjacencyMatrix[city2Id-1][city1Id-1] = budgetValue;
 :Log \"Budget added for the road between \" + city1Name + \" and \" + city2Name;
 else (no)
 :Log \"Error: No road exists between \" + city1Name + \" and \" + city2Name + \". Add road first.\";
 endif
 else (no)
 :Log \"Error: One or both cities not found, or cities are the same.\";
 endif
 case (4)
 :User selected \"Edit city\";
 :Prompt \"Enter the index of the city to edit:\";
 :User enters cityIndex;
 if (cityIndex valid in city list?) then (yes)
 :Prompt \"Enter new name for city \" + cityIndex + \":\";
 :User enters newCityName;
 :Validate newCityName (is it unique among OTHERS?);
 if (Unique or same as old name) then (yes)
 :Update city name for cityIndex;
 :Log \"City \" + cityIndex + \" updated successfully to \" + newCityName;
 else (no)
 :Log \"New city name already exists for another city.\";
 endif
 else (no)
 :Log \"Error: Invalid city index.\";
 endif
 case (5)
 :User selected \"Search for a city using its index\";
 :Prompt \"Enter city index to search:\";
 :User enters searchIndex;
 if (searchIndex valid in city list?) then (yes)
 :Display city details: \"City \" + searchIndex + \": \" + cityName;
 else (no)
 :Log \"Error: City with index \" + searchIndex + \" not found.\";
 endif
 case (6)
 :User selected \"Display cities\";
 :Display \"Cities:\";
 :For each city (id, name) in list;
 :Print id + \": \" + name;
 :EndFor;
 case (7)
 :User selected \"Display roads\";
 :Call \"Display cities\" routine (as per example);
 :Display \"Roads Adjacency Matrix:\";
 :Print header row of city indices (or names);
 :For each row i in roadAdjacencyMatrix;
 :Print city index i+1 (or name);
 :For each col j in row i;
 :Print roadAdjacencyMatrix[i][j];
 :EndFor;
 :Newline;
 :EndFor;
 case (8)
 :User selected \"Display recorded data on console\";
 :Call \"Display cities\" routine;
 :Call \"Display roads\" routine (road adjacency matrix);
 :Display \"Budgets Adjacency Matrix:\";
 :Print header row of city indices (or names);
 :For each row i in budgetAdjacencyMatrix;
 :Print city index i+1 (or name);
 :For each col j in row i;
 :Print budgetAdjacencyMatrix[i][j];
 :EndFor;
 :Newline;
 :EndFor;
 case (9)
 :User selected \"Exit\";
 :Save city list to cities.txt (Index, City_Name);
 :Save roads and budgets to roads.txt (Nbr, Road, Budget);
 :Log \"Exiting application. Data saved.\";
 stop
 case (default)
 :Log \"Invalid choice. Please try again.\";
 endswitch
repeat while (choice != 9)

end
@enduml",
